      • makeNumber

        public static TypedObject makeNumber(Object value)
        Takes a non-null value and returns a numeric TypedObject - it has a type in Type.NUMERICS. The value is then a Number. It uses the String representation of the object to cast it.
        Parameters:
        value - The Object value that is being cast to a numeric.
        Returns:
        The casted TypedObject with the type set to numeric or GENERIC_UNKNOWN if not.
